cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.SE

The paper proposes a new functional language that extends existing array calculi to support infinite arrays, which involves introducing ordinal numbers to shapes and indices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the expressibility of the proposed calculus with several examples, which suggests that it may also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses implementation-related challenges, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
